  const parsed = UserQuery.safeParse(req.params);
  if (!parsed.success) return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid id' });
  // ...
});
```

## 5. Sensitive data exposure on `/users`
The endpoint returns email addresses with no authentication, authorization, or pagination. Even with mock data this trains the wrong pattern. At minimum:

- Require auth (JWT/session middleware) before returning PII.
- Return a minimal projection (omit email unless the caller owns the record or is an admin).
- Support pagination (`?limit=&cursor=`) with caps, so a future DB-backed version can't be dumped in one call.

