app.set('trust proxy', 1);                 // if behind a reverse proxy
app.use(helmet());                         // secure HTTP headers
app.use(express.json({ limit: '100kb' })); // cap body size to prevent DoS
app.use(cors({ origin: process.env.ALLOWED_ORIGIN || false }));

app.use(rateLimit({
  windowMs: 60_000,
  max: 100,
  standardHeaders: true,
  legacyHeaders: false,
}));
```

## 4. Don't hard-code config / secrets

**Issue:** Port `3000` is hard-coded; future DB credentials, API keys, etc. should never be.

