## 1. Missing global error handling

There's no error-handling middleware, no `uncaughtException`/`unhandledRejection` handlers, and no handling of server startup failure (e.g., `EADDRINUSE`).

```js
// 404 handler — must come after all routes
app.use((req, res) => {
  res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' });
});

// Error-handling middleware — must have 4 args
app.use((err, req, res, _next) => {
  // Log internally, but don't leak stack traces to clients
  console.error(err);
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });
});

const server = app.listen(3000, () => { /* ... */ });
server.on('error', (err) => {
  console.error('Server failed to start:', err.message);
  process.exit(1);
});
```

## 2. No input validation on routes

Even though the current routes don't take parameters, any future `/users/:id` or query-string use needs validation. Adopt a schema validator up front:

