app.use(rateLimit({ windowMs: 60_000, max: 100, standardHeaders: true, legacyHeaders: false }));
```

## 5. Don't leak PII on an unauthenticated endpoint

`GET /users` currently returns real-looking emails with no authentication. Even with mock data, this shape trains consumers to expect an open endpoint. Either:

- Require authentication (e.g., JWT middleware), and/or
- Return only non-sensitive fields (`id`, `name`) by default and gate emails behind auth/scopes.

## 6. Graceful shutdown

Without graceful shutdown, in-flight requests can be cut off and sockets leaked on SIGTERM (common in containers):

```js
