### 1. No global error handling
Uncaught errors will crash the process or leak stack traces to clients.

### 2. Missing security middleware
No `helmet`, no rate limiting, no body size limits, no CORS policy.

### 3. No input validation
Endpoints don't validate query/path/body params — fine here since none are used, but the pattern isn't set up for when they're added.

