|---|---|
| Stack trace leakage | Central error handler returns generic 500 |
| DoS via large bodies | `express.json({ limit: '10kb' })` |
| DoS via request floods | `express-rate-limit` |
| Header-based attacks (clickjacking, MIME sniffing, etc.) | `helmet()` |
| Framework fingerprinting | `app.disable('x-powered-by')` |
| Input tampering | Schema validation (`zod` / `joi` / `ajv`) per route |
| PII exposure | Drop `email` from `/users`, add authN/authZ |
| Crash on startup errors | `server.on('error', …)` + port validation |
| Crash propagation | `unhandledRejection` / `uncaughtException` handlers |
| Deploy-time config | Read `PORT` from env and validate |

