## Critical gaps

### 1. No global error handler
Express silently crashes or leaks stack traces without an error-handling middleware. Any throw inside a route handler (or rejected async promise) will hit Express's default handler, which can expose internals in non-production environments.

```js
// Add at the end, after all routes:
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err); // replace with structured logger in prod
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({ error: 'Internal Server Error' });
});

