app.use((req, res) => res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not Found' }));
```

### 2. No security headers
Install and use `helmet` to set `X-Content-Type-Options`, `Strict-Transport-Security`, `X-Frame-Options`, CSP, etc.

```js
const helmet = require('helmet');
app.use(helmet());
```

### 3. No body-parsing limits
Even though current routes are GET-only, adding `express.json()` without a limit later invites DoS via huge payloads:

